---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const updated = "2026-06-19";
---

<BaseLayout title="Disclaimer" description="What Journal is and isn't.">
	<header class="container-prose page-head">
		<p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Journal</a> / <a href="/legal/">Legal</a> / Disclaimer</p>
		<h1>Disclaimer</h1>
		<p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
	</header>

	<article class="container-prose prose">
		<p>
			Journal is published in good faith for general personal-journaling use.
			Use it at your own risk.
		</p>

		<h2>Not therapy or medical advice</h2>
		<p>
			Mood tracking, gratitude prompts, and reflection journals can support
			your wellbeing, but they are not a substitute for consultation with a
			qualified mental-health professional or registered medical practitioner.
			If you are in crisis, please contact a helpline or doctor.
		</p>

		<h2>Not financial advice</h2>
		<p>
			Anything you write or track in a finance-themed journal is your own
			data. Journal does not provide investment, tax, or insurance advice.
		</p>

		<h2>Not legal advice</h2>
		<p>
			Articles touching on tax, regulation, or compliance reflect the author's
			reading of the rules at the time of writing. Rules change. Verify with
			your own counsel before acting.
		</p>

		<h2>Data durability</h2>
		<p>
			Journal stores your entries in Firebase Firestore. We expect Firestore to
			be highly available, but no service is perfect. <strong>Export your data
			regularly</strong> — Settings → Export gives you JSON / Markdown / ZIP at any
			time. We are not liable for entries lost due to browser, network, or
			third-party-service failure.
		</p>

		<h2>External links</h2>
		<p>
			We link to third-party sites (Firebase docs, oriz family, GitHub) we
			find useful. We don't control their content, and inclusion is not an
			endorsement.
		</p>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.page-head {
		padding-block: 3rem 1.5rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule, #d9d0bd);
	}
	.eyebrow {
		color: var(--color-ink-muted, #6b6256);
		font-size: 0.8125rem;
		margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
	}
	.eyebrow a { color: var(--color-ink-muted, #6b6256); text-decoration: none; }
	h1 {
		font-family: var(--font-display, "Fraunces", serif);
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.meta { color: var(--color-ink-subtle, #9a9082); font-size: 0.875rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0; }
	.prose {
		padding-block: 2.5rem 4rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		font-size: 1.0625rem;
	}
	.prose h2 {
		font-family: var(--font-display, "Fraunces", serif);
		font-size: 1.375rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
	}
	.prose p { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
	.prose a { color: var(--color-sienna, #b45309); }
	.container-prose {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin-inline: auto;
		padding-inline: clamp(1rem, 4vw, 2rem);
	}
</style>
